id: pm-m4ov
title: Profile and optimize command startup latency
description: "Follow-up from 2026-05-10 dogfood audit: core agent-loop commands still take roughly 0.5-1.7s in an isolated temp project. Profile startup/runtime initialization, defer nonessential work for read-only commands, and add an automated dogfood benchmark with thresholds."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: agent-ux,dogfood,performance,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-10T21:50:47.973Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-10T22:50:42.739Z"
author: codex-agent
acceptance_criteria: A benchmark covers init/create/list/context/search/calendar/health; startup hot paths are profiled; read-only commands avoid nonessential extension/telemetry/vector work; representative local commands feel sub-second where feasible.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Optimized startup telemetry flushing and semantic reindex hot path; added lock-dir resilience and CI cleanup stability.
expected_result: "Common pm commands stay responsive, unchanged semantic reindex avoids redundant embedding work, and regression coverage plus CI stay green."
actual_result: "Default telemetry benchmark commands complete in roughly 0.6-0.8s, unchanged hybrid reindex completes in 869ms for 686 items, coverage/static/docs/secrets/CI passed."
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-10T21:50:47.973Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: ran pm search startup performance instant command benchmark lazy initialization --limit 10. Only closed historical performance/search items matched; no open item covers current command startup latency benchmark work."
  "2026-05-10T22:26:13.341Z",codex-agent,"CI follow-up: GitHub run 25641271233 failed only on macOS Node 20 in tests/unit/comments-command.spec.ts with ENOTEMPTY while removing the temporary .agents/pm tree. Added a bounded ENOTEMPTY/EBUSY/EPERM retry to tests/helpers/withTempPmPath.ts and kept the in-progress incremental semantic reindex + lock-directory guard changes. Local focused verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/comments-command.spec.ts tests/unit/reindex-command.spec.ts tests/unit/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts (72 tests)."
  "2026-05-10T22:50:21.402Z",codex-agent,"Evidence: latest audit/performance pass completed on 2026-05-10. Changes shipped in 24731a2 and 66e0647 keep production telemetry responsive via detached flush worker, add reindex locking, create missing lock dirs defensively, and skip unchanged semantic embeddings. Temp-project dogfood passed init/create/claim/update/comment/files/docs/test/list/context/search/calendar/aggregate/dedupe/contracts/extension/health/validate/close/release with sandboxed PM_PATH and PM_GLOBAL_PATH. Startup benchmark after the telemetry change: pm --version 608ms, init 597ms, list-open 655ms, context 730ms, calendar 635ms, search 835ms, health 665ms with queue drained. Hybrid reindex on current tracker: 686 loaded, 686 unchanged embeddings skipped, completed in 869ms. Verification passed: focused reindex/telemetry/release-readiness tests, lock coverage tests, search-cache focused test, serial full coverage 90 files/1276 tests at 100%, pnpm quality:static, pnpm quality:docs-skills, node scripts/check-secrets.mjs, git diff --check, and main CI run 25641740951 green across macOS/Windows/Ubuntu matrix. Health/validate remaining findings are pre-existing tracker hygiene warnings: history drift on five legacy items and one resolution metadata warning. Remote telemetry stack was live with queue depth 0, active consumer, and recent events; Sentry still has unresolved historical groups including a scrubbed latest high-priority import error."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-10T21:50:47.973Z",codex-agent,"Dogfood final timings on 2026-05-10 still showed init 1387ms, create about 1.1s, list-open 1209ms, context 1051ms, keyword search 1015ms, calendar 1411ms, health 1754ms."
